 in Heaven, it’s freedom. When Christ mocks Satan, it isn’t insecurity speaking. It’s sovereignty.</p><p>Jesus called Herod “that fox.” He told demons to shut up and go home. He let evil boast, perform, and posture, and then defeated it in silence.</p><p>And after the grave swallowed Him, He rose. Not timidly. Not politely. But with a grin that split the tomb in two.</p><h3><strong>Triumph as Theater</strong></h3><p>The Apostle Paul writes that Jesus “disarmed the rulers and authorities and made a public specta…</p>"}